data.title: Prince Edward of Wales opens the Victoria Memorial, Kolkata: Edward, Prince of Wales. Royal Tour of India, 1921
data.meta_description: Photograph of Prince Edward of Wales standing on a chequered terrace floor as he opens the new Victoria memorial in Kolkata (Calcutta). Seated on either side of the Prince is the Earl of Ronaldshay (1876-1961), Governor of Bengal and his wife Lady Cicely Ronaldshay, neé Archdale (1886-1973) both of whom are seated. Standing behind the Prince are uniformed officers. Seated behind the Prince is likely Sir Bijay Chand Mahtab, Maharajadhiraja Bahadur of Burdwan.The Victoria memorial is built...
